%N A039377 Numbers whose base-9 representation has the same nonzero number of 2's and 8's.
%H A039377 Chris R. Rehmann, <a href="/A039377/b039377.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%t A039377 Select[Range[953], DigitCount[#, 9, 2]==DigitCount[#, 9, 8]>0&] (* _Chris R. Rehmann_, Apr 10 2026 *)
%o A039377 (MATLAB) x = 0:953; d = dec2base(x,9)-'0'; s1 = sum(d==2,2); s2 = sum(d==8,2); a = x(s1==s2 & s1>0); disp(regexprep(num2str(a), ' +', ', ')) % _Chris R. Rehmann_, Apr 10 2026
